OL,3,CHorizon scandal: Cleared Post Office
OL,4,Cclerk 'shunned by village community'
OL,6,FThe ex-Post Office clerk had been
OL,7,Fattempting to cover up a #933.69
OL,8,Fshortfall in the branch's accounts,
OL,9,Fwhich she had not taken and could not
OL,10,Fexplain but feared would be deducted
OL,11,Ffrom her wages, the court heard.
OL,13,FShe was handed a three-month prison
OL,14,Fsentence, suspended for 12 months, and
OL,15,Fordered to pay #933.69 in compensation
OL,16,Fafter pleading guilty to fraud at
OL,17,FNewcastle Crown Court in 2015.
